{
  "stem": "8775.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this was a time when I heard about my father and my mother heard about my father as well, his tragic situation, what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, from Budapest we were sent by this committee to Szolnok, where we used to live.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was very mixed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Lots of people said that more came back than they left before in 1944, which was terrible to hear.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And on the railroad trains you heard these expressions and the hate within their eyes and their voices.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there were some other ones who knew my father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they came over in the streets of Szolnok to me and they expressed their sorrow and their condolences about the loss of my father.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were people who obviously were either clients of his or knew him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, they knew the whole family, as I said, because my family used to live there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And his great-grandfather, everybody lived in Szolnok.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My home was no longer there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our furniture was no longer there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some of the things, which were like my accordion, which I had just kept gotten for my birthday in 1944 and I gave it to my mother's aunt, that was taken.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were all pretty much financially as well devastated at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And had it not been for the help of the American Joint Distribution Committee, I don't know what would have happened with us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think we received clothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We received food, received a lot of food from the American Jewish Committee, from the Joint.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my mother actually got a job, which was her first job ever in her life, working for the American Joint Committee in Szolnok, where she was like involved in the storage of the items and distribution of the items.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
